				<td colspan="2"><span>the best info i've seen is on the eq 2 boards:
<br />

<br />
<a target="_new" href="http://eqiiforums.station.sony.com/eq2/board?board.id=scout">http://eqiiforums.station.sony.com/eq2/board?board.id=scout</a>
<br />

<br />
as far as songs and class abilities go, although the list is incomplete, you can get a general idea here:
<br />

<br />
<a target="_new" href="http://eq2vault.ign.com">http://eq2vault.ign.com</a> 
<br />

<br />
from what i understand, you can keep up five concentration counters, so your number of songs is limited by how much concentration a song takes.  i think the troubadour charm, for example, currently takes 5 counters.
<br />

<br />
anyone have any impressions on the play style of the new bards (dirge vs troubadour, soloability, group desirability)?  which current class is most bard-like in terms of versatility/flexibility from the eq1 perspective?  what are player-crafted instruments like (about all i've seen is this thread: <a target="_new" href="http://eqiiforums.station.sony.com/eq2/board/message?board.id=artisan&amp;message.id=2965&amp;highlight=instrument+crafting#M2965">http://eqiiforums.station.sony.com/eq2/board/message?board.id=artisan&amp;message.id=2965&amp;highlight=instrument+crafting#M2965</a> ).</span></td>
