			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: EQ2 bard<a name="67538"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 20 04 12:21 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Now that the NDA is lifted, I can tell you guys a bit.
<br />

<br />
I have a 21 Troubador in Beta.  eq2 Bards are NOT eq1 Bards, but then eq2 is NOT eq1!  
<br />

<br />
Things change rapidly and frequently in Beta, so it's hard to say really how solo play will be.  A patch or two ago, players got nerfed, and NPCs got a boost.  Today's patch (which I haven't played yet, hehe) says that NPCs will now be much better at using their Spells and Combat Arts.  That could be quite scary, hehe, and they may need to tune things yet again.  They also added more &quot;Solo-marked&quot; content with last week's patch in response to player requests.
<br />

<br />
Scouts are, imo, the most challenging and complex class in the game.  That's partly why I decided to play a Bard again, in spite of the radically different role and flavor eq2 Bards have.
<br />

<br />
Scouts are primarily melee DPS, and that includes Bards.  When you get to the Class and Subclass levels, you will see Bards/Dirges/Troubadors lose some outright melee dps compared to Predator/Ranger/Assassins, for example.  But we get group buffs, haste, and other cool stuff that makes a big difference in groups.  Again, a similar role of force multiplier.
<br />

<br />
Troubadors will get Charm (it's broken atm, hehe) and Mez.  Dirges get Fear (no idea how it works yet) and a non-combat rez.  Other than that, Troubadors get more group buffs, while Dirges get more enemy debuffs.
<br />

<br />
Instruments are not fully implemented at this time.  No one is really sure what they will do.  They do not equip, and I can't figure out what the point is, lol.  I DID make some though!  I have a set of Maple instruments I made, hehe.
<br />

<br />
Tradeskills are less tedious than eq1, and they are tweaking them all the time, trying to make them even less of a grind.  (While the activity is less boring than eq1 tradeskills, it can put you to sleep nonetheless, lol.)
<br />

<br />
Not sure what else to say at this point.  Ask any questions you like, I guess, hehe.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
