				<td colspan="2"><span>Ok, had to edit this considerably to TRY to make it comprehensible.  The original is all color-coded and slick.
<br />

<br />
It is worth noting that among all the archetype, only Scouts have more than ONE Starter Chain, Cloak and Dagger.
<br />

<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">Thank you to all who contributed !
<br />
 
<br />
Heroic Opportunites seem to have gotten quite some tuning. That made the old thread obsolote. Please post here about Heroic Opportunities your found including their Starter Chain and the results. So we can help balancing them:
<br />
 
<br />
This is a work in progress. So please continue to contribute and correct any errors. Thank you.
<br />
 
<br />
First read this: http://eqiiforums.station.sony.com/eq2/board/message?board.id=bspells&amp;message.id=995
<br />
(for color coding see this thread) Examine your spells/art (right click on icon, choose Examine). Most of the spells/arts have 2 icons. The first is the icon which also appears on your tool bar or in the knowledge book. The 2nd icon represents the group the spell belongs too. These icons are used to create Starter Chains and Heroic opportunities.
<br />
 
<br />
As a scout, you have the option before anyone starts on an active HO wheel to try to change it to another in the same chain. So if you see the common is up, you can use coin to try to &quot;switch the wheel&quot; and possibly get the uncommon or rare.
<br />
 
<br />
