				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: EQ2 bard<a name="67643"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 20 04 10:33 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>About the relative importance of Heroic Opportunities...
<br />

<br />
They are a tremendous boon to solo play, often making the difference in whether you win or lose.  Groups are another matter.
<br />

<br />
There are a handful of people who HATE the HOs.  They see it as a silly game of Simon or &quot;Whack-a-Mole&quot; that doesn't belong in the game.  (I disagree, hehe).  The most vehement opposition comes mostly from the two most one-demensional classes in the game:  fighters and priests.  &quot;I'm not gonna let someone die just because the stupid flashing lights told me do do something other than heal...&quot;
<br />

<br />
There is also, especially at lower levels, a heavy PLOW mentality among many players.  Because combat is SO fast paced, people will often just Blow their proverbial load and try to empty their power bar in an outpouring of dps...  This gets better though as you level up.
<br />

<br />
And then there are people who will complain and pick if others in the group don't do the HO Starter Chains right etc.
<br />

<br />
I will always attempt to get the groups I am in to at least plan and execute ONE HO on the pull.  I see no reason why this is not doable.  No one should be dying in the first 15 seconds of combat.  Too often though, either people don't understand how the Starter Chains work, don't know their &quot;runes&quot; (the freakin buttons flash the right ones, lol), or they are too itchy to start hacking, slashing, and nuking.
<br />

<br />
In conclusion, groups will OFTEN fight and play with total disregard to the HOs, and they do just fine.  You do NOT &quot;need&quot; to do HOs to do even-con group content with a well balanced group.  If the group is smaller (4 people for example) or NOT balanced, they can make a big difference.  It makes combat a LOT more fun too, imo.
<br />

<br />
Screw waiting, Krescendo!  Even with stuff as messed up as it is currently in Beta it is SO much fun, I pretty much forgot my eq1 Bard.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
